									<DEFAULT-VALUE>false</DEFAULT-VALUE>
								</ECUC-BOOLEAN-PARAM-DEF>
								<ECUC-BOOLEAN-PARAM-DEF UUID="7561d8d6-c79a-4e87-bd1d-6bdc23fd8cbb">
									<SHORT-NAME>vBRSEnableSchmStubGeneration</SHORT-NAME>
									<LONG-NAME>
										<L-4 L="EN">Generation of SchM Stub</L-4>
									</LONG-NAME>
									<DESC>
										<L-2 L="EN">Activate this, if the SchM stubs, containing the defines for EXCLUSIVE AREAs, should be generated. Needed, if the ASR RTE/SchM is not part of the configuration, but modules are using the SchM exclusive area mechanism.</L-2>
									</DESC>
									<ADMIN-DATA>
										<SDGS>
											<SDG GID="DV:CfgPostBuild">
												<SD GID="DV:variantMultiplicityPBL">false</SD>
											</SDG>
										</SDGS>
									</ADMIN-DATA>
									<LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
									<UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
									<IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIG-CLASSES>
										<ECUC-IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
											<CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
											<CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
										</ECUC-IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
									</IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIG-CLASSES>
									<ORIGIN>Vector Informatik</ORIGIN>
									<REQUIRES-INDEX>false</REQUIRES-INDEX>
									<SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>false</SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>
									<DEFAULT-VALUE>false</DEFAULT-VALUE>
								</ECUC-BOOLEAN-PARAM-DEF>
								<ECUC-BOOLEAN-PARAM-DEF UUID="5b5a84da-099c-48ea-b263-75d9f455b97e">
									<SHORT-NAME>vBRSEnableSchmStubSupportDrvCanAN</SHORT-NAME>
									<LONG-NAME>
										<L-4 L="EN">Generation of SchM Stub - support DrvCan AN</L-4>
									</LONG-NAME>
									<DESC>
										<L-2 L="EN">Prevents the SchM stub from generation of the following exclusive areas:
CAN Driver (CAN_EXCLUSIVE_AREA_6) 
CAN Interface (CANIF_EXCLUSIVE_AREA_0) 
CANSM (CANSM_ EXCLUSIVE_AREA_1, CANSM_ EXCLUSIVE_AREA_4) 
COMM (COMM_ EXCLUSIVE_AREA_1)
As described within CanDriver ApplicationNote AN-ISC-8-1149.
The implementation of these APIs, under consideration of this AN, is already part of static BrsMain_Appl.c.</L-2>
									</DESC>
									<ADMIN-DATA>
										<SDGS>
											<SDG GID="DV:CfgPostBuild">
												<SD GID="DV:variantMultiplicityPBL">false</SD>
											</SDG>
										</SDGS>
									</ADMIN-DATA>
									<LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
									<UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
									<IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIG-CLASSES>
										<ECUC-IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
											<CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
											<CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
										</ECUC-IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
									</IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIG-CLASSES>
									<ORIGIN>Vector Informatik</ORIGIN>
									<REQUIRES-INDEX>false</REQUIRES-INDEX>
									<SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>false</SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>
									<DEFAULT-VALUE>true</DEFAULT-VALUE>
								</ECUC-BOOLEAN-PARAM-DEF>
								<ECUC-BOOLEAN-PARAM-DEF UUID="d4e04271-7fea-4e7c-b458-4ad97dff2c01">
									<SHORT-NAME>vBRSEnableSchmStubEmptyExclusiveAreaHandling</SHORT-NAME>
									<LONG-NAME>
										<L-4 L="EN">Generation of SchM Stub - empty exclusive area handling</L-4>
									</LONG-NAME>
									<DESC>
										<L-2 L="EN">For normal, all module specific exclusive are calls are mapped to SuspendAllInterrupts()/ResumeAllInterrupts().
If this feature is activated, the SchM stub will generate them as empty calls instead.
E.g. in SchM_Mcu.h:
# define SchM_Enter_Mcu_MCU_EXCLUSIVE_AREA_00()
# define SchM_Exit_Mcu_MCU_EXCLUSIVE_AREA_00()
instead of
# define SchM_Enter_Mcu_MCU_EXCLUSIVE_AREA_00() SuspendAllInterrupts()
# define SchM_Exit_Mcu_MCU_EXCLUSIVE_AREA_00() ResumeAllInterrupts()

This is mainly for polling environments, where no OS is used and therefore no specific disabling of interrupts is necessary.</L-2>
									</DESC>
									<ADMIN-DATA>
										<SDGS>
											<SDG GID="DV:CfgPostBuild">
												<SD GID="DV:variantMultiplicityPBL">false</SD>
											</SDG>
										</SDGS>
									</ADMIN-DATA>
									<LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
									<UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
									<IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIG-CLASSES>
										<ECUC-IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
											<CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
											<CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
										</ECUC-IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
									</IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIG-CLASSES>
									<ORIGIN>Vector Informatik</ORIGIN>
									<REQUIRES-INDEX>false</REQUIRES-INDEX>
									<SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>false</SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>
									<DEFAULT-VALUE>false</DEFAULT-VALUE>
								</ECUC-BOOLEAN-PARAM-DEF>
								<ECUC-ENUMERATION-PARAM-DEF UUID="75ff9472-6359-4afd-bf37-fffce3c3ad82">
									<SHORT-NAME>vBRSExecutionInstance</SHORT-NAME>
									<LONG-NAME>
										<L-4 L="EN">This executable: Execution Instance</L-4>
									</LONG-NAME>
									<DESC>
										<L-2 L="EN">Configure the execution instance of the application, handled by this configuration.
As sometimes, there exist several applications in one system, they need to be separated.
"Application" stands for a "normal" application executable (e.g. MSR or CANbedded stack), which could be standalone or called out of a FBL or BM.
"FBL" stands for a FlashBootLoader executable, which could be standalone or called out of a BM.
"FBL_Updater" stands for a FlashBootLoader Updater executable, which could be standalone or called out of a BM.
"BM" stands for a Boot Manager executable, which is the startup entry and decides to call a FBL, Updater or Application.
"BM_FBL" stands for a Boot Manager and FlashBootLoader executable, which are compiled together. The BootManager part is the startup entry and decides to call the FBL part, Updater or Application.
"HSM" stands for a HSM Core executable, which could be standalone or called out of a BM (if also a HSM updater is present).
"FlashDriver" stands for a standalone binary, containing a flasher driver instance only. There is no runtime part included.

Sets the following generated parameters in vBrsCfg.h:
BRS_ENABLE_FBL for the values "FBL", "FBL_Updater", "BM" and "BM_FBL"
BRS_ENABLE_HSM_SUPPORT for the value "HSM"

Sets the following generated parameters in Makefile.config.generated:
BRS_ENABLE_HSM_SUPPORT, BRS_ENABLE_FBL_SUPPORT</L-2>
									</DESC>
									<ADMIN-DATA>
										<SDGS>
											<SDG GID="DV:CfgPostBuild">
												<SD GID="DV:variantMultiplicityPBL">false</SD>
											</SDG>
										</SDGS>
									</ADMIN-DATA>
									<LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
									<UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
									<IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIG-CLASSES>
										<ECUC-IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
											<CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
											<CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
										</ECUC-IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
									</IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIG-CLASSES>
									<ORIGIN>Vector Informatik</ORIGIN>
									<REQUIRES-INDEX>false</REQUIRES-INDEX>
									<SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>false</SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>
									<DEFAULT-VALUE>Application</DEFAULT-VALUE>
									<LITERALS>
										<ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF UUID="716a6e57-2b9f-4c98-b930-cccfed4d2dfe">
											<SHORT-NAME>Application</SHORT-NAME>
											<LONG-NAME>
												<L-4 L="EN">normal application instance</L-4>
											</LONG-NAME>
											<ORIGIN>Vector Informatik</ORIGIN>
										</ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF>
										<ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF UUID="5f217cc1-1502-4156-9e84-7603e0d37903">
											<SHORT-NAME>FBL</SHORT-NAME>
											<LONG-NAME>
												<L-4 L="EN">FBL instance</L-4>
											</LONG-NAME>
											<ORIGIN>Vector Informatik</ORIGIN>
										</ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF>
										<ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF UUID="ce05bdd8-206b-4182-8a85-18be69219afa">
											<SHORT-NAME>FBL_Updater</SHORT-NAME>
											<LONG-NAME>
												<L-4 L="EN">FBL Updater instance</L-4>
											</LONG-NAME>
											<ORIGIN>Vector Informatik</ORIGIN>
										</ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF>
										<ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF UUID="22473713-0de1-4f29-ae0b-c121eb54fa95">
											<SHORT-NAME>BM</SHORT-NAME>
											<LONG-NAME>
												<L-4 L="EN">BM instance</L-4>
											</LONG-NAME>
											<ORIGIN>Vector Informatik</ORIGIN>
										</ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF>
										<ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF UUID="6be61047-9811-4b8d-9c1a-f6710267e942">
											<SHORT-NAME>BM_FBL</SHORT-NAME>
											<LONG-NAME>
												<L-4 L="EN">BM+FBL combined instance</L-4>
											</LONG-NAME>
											<ORIGIN>Vector Informatik</ORIGIN>
										</ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF>
										<ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF UUID="631db45e-381a-46b5-8e34-9315e7879d2a">
											<SHORT-NAME>HSM</SHORT-NAME>
											<LONG-NAME>
												<L-4 L="EN">HSM instance</L-4>
											</LONG-NAME>
											<ORIGIN>Vector Informatik</ORIGIN>
										</ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF>
										<ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF UUID="9236bb78-5778-40da-bbc9-851985637775">
											<SHORT-NAME>FlashDriver</SHORT-NAME>
											<LONG-NAME>
												<L-4 L="EN">FBL FlashDriver instance</L-4>
											</LONG-NAME>
											<ORIGIN>Vector Informatik</ORIGIN>
										</ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF>
									</LITERALS>
								</ECUC-ENUMERATION-PARAM-DEF>
								<ECUC-BOOLEAN-PARAM-DEF UUID="79064ffe-a1dd-4097-b0d9-fb5e5c4fd36c">
									<SHORT-NAME>vBRSFirstInstance</SHORT-NAME>
									<LONG-NAME>
										<L-4 L="EN">This executable: First execution instance in system</L-4>
									</LONG-NAME>
									<DESC>
										<L-2 L="EN">Configure, if this executable is the first instance of the system.
Set this parameter to enabled, if this instance should contain the brsStartupEntry and initialize the core.
Only one single executable of a system with several executables should be the first instance. All other executables are starting with Brs_ApplicationEntry().
E.g. in a FBL UseCase with standalone BM, the BM is the first executable and the FBL, Updater, MSR-Application are not.
If there is only a single executable in the system, of course this application is also the first one.

Sets the following generated parameters:
BRS_FIRST_EXECUTION_INSTANCE in vBrsCfg.h</L-2>
									</DESC>
									<ADMIN-DATA>
										<SDGS>
											<SDG GID="DV:CfgPostBuild">
												<SD GID="DV:variantMultiplicityPBL">false</SD>
											</SDG>
										</SDGS>
									</ADMIN-DATA>
									<LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
									<UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
									<IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIG-CLASSES>
										<ECUC-IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
											<CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
											<CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
										</ECUC-IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
									</IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIG-CLASSES>
									<ORIGIN>Vector Informatik</ORIGIN>
									<REQUIRES-INDEX>false</REQUIRES-INDEX>
									<SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>false</SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>
									<DEFAULT-VALUE>true</DEFAULT-VALUE>
								</ECUC-BOOLEAN-PARAM-DEF>
								<ECUC-BOOLEAN-PARAM-DEF UUID="f3f8d8e2-bf36-4b86-b7c1-df38ce24843a">
									<SHORT-NAME>vBRSEnableCoreSpecificVLinkGenConfig</SHORT-NAME>
									<LONG-NAME>
										<L-4 L="EN">Enable core specific vLinkGen config validation</L-4>
									</LONG-NAME>
									<DESC>
										<L-2 L="EN">Enable the validation of core specific vLinkGen config data based on cores configured within /EcuC/EcucHardware/EcucCoreDefinitions and /Os/OsCores.</L-2>
									</DESC>
									<ADMIN-DATA>
										<SDGS>
											<SDG GID="DV:CfgPostBuild">
												<SD GID="DV:variantMultiplicityPBL">false</SD>
											</SDG>
										</SDGS>
									</ADMIN-DATA>
									<LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
									<UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
									<IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIG-CLASSES>
										<ECUC-IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
											<CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
											<CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
										</ECUC-IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
									</IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIG-CLASSES>
									<ORIGIN>Vector Informatik</ORIGIN>
									<REQUIRES-INDEX>false</REQUIRES-INDEX>
									<SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>false</SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>
									<DEFAULT-VALUE>false</DEFAULT-VALUE>
								</ECUC-BOOLEAN-PARAM-DEF>
								<ECUC-BOOLEAN-PARAM-DEF UUID="007687b4-bfa3-49be-b6a7-e8a7dfa2a855">
									<SHORT-NAME>vBRSFblSupportEcuMInit</SHORT-NAME>
									<LONG-NAME>
										<L-4 L="EN">This executable: FBL/BM support with EcuMInit</L-4>
									</LONG-NAME>
									<DESC>
										<L-2 L="EN">Configure, if the FBL stack should be started inside main() via a call of EcuM_Init() or a call of FblMain().
This parameter only has an effect, if Execution Instance is "FBL", "FBL_Updater", "BM" or "BM_FBL".
FBL without EcuM_Init() is the oldstyle FBL integration, started with a direct call of FblMain().
FBL with EcuM_Init() means, module initialization is done in EcuM_Init() (real EcuM or EcuM Stub), but the cyclic handling is done in FBL.

Sets the following generated parameters:
BRS_FBL_WITH_ECUMINIT or BRS_FBL_NO_ECUMINIT in vBrsCfg.h</L-2>
									</DESC>
									<ADMIN-DATA>
										<SDGS>
											<SDG GID="DV:CfgPostBuild">
												<SD GID="DV:variantMultiplicityPBL">false</SD>
											</SDG>
										</SDGS>
									</ADMIN-DATA>
									<LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
									<UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
									<IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIG-CLASSES>
										<ECUC-IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
											<CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
											<CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
										</ECUC-IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
									</IMPLEMENTATION-CONFIG-CLASSES>
									<ORIGIN>Vector Informatik</ORIGIN>
									<REQUIRES-INDEX>false</REQUIRES-INDEX>
									<SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>false</SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>
									<DEFAULT-VALUE>false</DEFAULT-VALUE>
								</ECUC-BOOLEAN-PARAM-DEF>
								<ECUC-BOOLEAN-PARAM-DEF UUID="7361ac9d-524f-4ff4-8bd3-3e012b151238">
									<SHORT-NAME>vBRSFblSupportExceptionTableInRam</SHORT-NAME>
									<LONG-NAME>
										<L-4 L="EN">This executable: FBL/BM exception table in RAM</L-4>
									</LONG-NAME>
									<DESC>
										<L-2 L="EN">Configure, if the additional ExceptionTable in RAM should be initialized. This will cause a call of BrsHw_ExceptionTable_Init() in main(), which will program the vector table base address to Brs_ExcVectRam. The depending SectionGroup needs to be configured with Init Policy COPY_TO_RAM in vLinkGen as well.
This allows proper exception handling during erase/re-program of flash.
The parameter only has an effect, if Execution Instance is "FBL", "FBL_Updater", "BM" or "BM_FBL".

Sets the following generated parameter:
BRS_FBL_EXCEPTIONTABLE_IN_RAM in vBrsCfg.h</L-2>
									</DESC>
									<ADMIN-DATA>
										<SDGS>
											<SDG GID="DV:CfgPostBuild">
												<SD GID="DV:variantMultiplicityPBL">false</SD>
											</SDG>
										</SDGS>
									</ADMIN-DATA>
